


Liverpool 1-1 Chelsea
Sunday 19th August 2007
Barclays Premier League
Attendance: 43,924
Referee: Robert Styles (Hampshire).

LIVERPOOL FOOTBALL CLUB GOALSCORER: Fernando Torres (16th minute).
CHELSEA FOOTBALL CLUB GOALSCORER: Frank Lampard (62nd minute -
PENALTY).

TEAMS:
LFC: Reina, Finnan, Carragher, Agger, Arbeloa, Pennant (Babel 68),
Gerrard, Alonso, Riise (Crouch 83), Torres, Kuyt.
CFC: Cech, Essien, Ben-Haim, Terry, Ashley Cole, Kalou (Pizarro 46),
Wright-Phillips (Joe Cole 77), Obi, Lampard, Malouda (Alex 85),
Drogba.

OTHER MATCH FACTS:
* Fernando Torres scored his first goal for Liverpool in this game.
